    "comment": "Rationale: - Overexpression of LRRTM4-Fc decreases excitatory synapse density in DIV14 hippocampal neurons (Figure 5, Myc-tagged LRRTM4).\n- Synaptogenic activity of LRRTM4 in HEK cells (Figures 6A-6D). (HEK cells, Myc-tagged LRRTM4).\n- LRRTM4 knockdown significantly decreases the density of dendritic protrusions in vivo and reduced synaptic currents (ctx neurons, shRNA KD).\n\n24/5/2017 Pim\n- All points to a role of LRRTM4 in synapse assembly (aka synapse formation) via a trans-synaptic interaction with GPC4.. Experimental description: Fig.5 \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from P0 Long-Evans **rats** (Charles River) \"\nFig.5+6 (Suppl.Info.): \"HEK293T cells were transfected with myc-tagged mouse LRRTM4\" The overexpression construct is of **mouse** species.\nFig.8: \"Embryonic day 15.5 mouse embryos were electroporated with control or shLRRTM4 plasmids, \"\n\n24/5/2017 Pim\nBecause of the species of the OE construct and the experiments in mice the annotated species should be mouse.",
